.TH XTI-IP 3 "$Date: 2004/03/01 02:44:05 $" "$Name:  $" "X/Open Transport Interface"
.SH "NAME"
.B xti_ip
\- X/Open Transport Interface \- Corrigendum for Internet Protocol (IP) Conformance
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.PP
.B #include <xti.h>
.br
.B #include <xti_ip.h>
.br
.B #include <xti_inet.h>
.HP
.BI "int " ip_stream " = t_open(" ip_device ", " flags );
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
.SH "OPTIONS"
.PP
.SS "T_INET_IP"
.PP
.TP 12
.B T_IP_OPTIONS
IP per-packet options.
.TP 12
.B T_IP_TOS
IP per-packet type of service.
.RS
.PP
.BI SET_TOS( prec ", " tos )
.PP
.I prec
can be one of the following values:
.RS
.TP 12
.I T_ROUTINE
.TP 12
.I T_PRIORITY
.TP 12
.I T_IMMEDIATE
.TP 12
.I T_FLASH
.TP 12
.I T_OVERRIDEFLASH
.TP 12
.I T_CRITIC_ECP
.TP 12
.I T_INETCONTROL
.TP 12
.I T_NETCONTROL
.RE
.PP
.I tos
can be one of the following values:
.RS
.TP 12
.I T_NOTOS
.TP 12
.I T_LDELAY
.TP 12
.I T_HITHRPT
.TP 12
.I T_HIREL
.TP 12
.I T_LOCOST
.RE
.RE
.TP 12
.B T_IP_TTL
IP per-packet time to live.
.TP 12
.B T_IP_REUSEADDR
Allow local address reuse.
.TP 12
.B T_IP_DONTROUTE
Just use interface address.
.TP 12
.B T_IP_BROADCAST
Permit sending of broadcast messages.
.SH "NOTES"
.PP
Including the
.B <xti_inet.h>
header file may include the
.B <xti_ip.h>
header file.
.SH "DEVICES"
.PP
There are a number of IP devices providng the Transport Provider Interface
that provide IP conforming TPI devices as follows:
.TP 12
.IR /dev/ip ", " /dev/inet/ip
.TP 12
.IR /dev/icmp ", " /dev/inet/icmp
.TP 12
.IR /dev/ggp ", " /dev/inet/ggp
.TP 12
.IR /dev/ipip ", " /dev/inet/ipip
.TP 12
.IR /dev/egp ", " /dev/inet/egp
.TP 12
.IR /dev/pup ", " /dev/inet/pup
.TP 12
.IR /dev/idp ", " /dev/inet/idp
.TP 12
.IR /dev/rawip ", " /dev/inet/rawip
.PP
These devices are provided by the
.B strinet
package.
.SH "CONFORMING TO"
.PP
The Open Group XNS Issue 5.2.
